If you have any problem when you use this skill, you can contact us with email : b.nahler@wesmartify.de
Amazon Alexa and the Essentials products work together to help you control home appliance nice and easy.
You can simply ask Alexa to turn on, turn off the device. 

There’s no need to go to the switch to adjust you light - just talk to Alexa on your Amazon Echo, Echo Dot, Amazon Tap or Echo Show. 
After connecting Alexa to your Essentials products in a few simple steps:
(1). Download our "essentials Smart Home" app in android or ios app market;
(2). Register one essentials Smart Home account in our "essentials Smart Home" app;
(3). You need to have some essentials Smart Home devices in hand;
(4). Configure these devices in our “essentials Smart Home" app and change appropriate name for your devices which will be used in "Essentials" skills;
(5). Download Amazon "Alexa" app from android,ios or Amazon app market;
(6). Configure Echo with "Alexa" app;
(7). Search "Essentials" skill from the "Alexa" app skills category;
(8). Click Enable skill of "Essentials", and you'll be navigated to essentials Smart Home login page;
(9). Input your essentials Smart Home account username and password, you'll be redirect to the success page;
(10). Now all setup is finished. 
You can enjoy the voice control on your home devices like these:

“Alexa, turn on smart light"
“Alexa, turn off smart light"
